2
00:00:40.523 --> 00:00:42.559
[insects chittering]

3
00:00:45.897 --> 00:00:47.865
[car approaching]

4
00:00:47.899 --> 00:00:49.599
[brakes squeaking]

5
00:00:50.949 --> 00:00:55.949
<font color="#ffff00">Provided by explosiveskull</font>
https://twitter.com/kaboomskull

6
00:01:03.114 --> 00:01:05.749
[car doors open. close]

7
00:01:37.014 --> 00:01:39.250
[dog barking]

8
00:01:39.283 --> 00:01:40.684
[whispering]
Someone's home.

9
00:01:43.020 --> 00:01:44.821
Supposed to be
on vacation.

10
00:01:47.191 --> 00:01:48.926
Fuck it. we're here now.

11
00:02:16.287 --> 00:02:18.822
- What are you doing in my house?
- [Wendy] Kyle?

12
00:02:18.856 --> 00:02:20.724
- Dad. Mom!
- Go.

13
00:02:28.866 --> 00:02:30.167
[siren chirps]

14
00:02:41.678 --> 00:02:44.547
[helicopter whirring]

15
00:03:11.976 --> 00:03:14.045
House smelled of death
the second we opened the door.

16
00:03:14.078 --> 00:03:17.314
The rook is still in the
bathroom coughing up lunch.

17
00:03:18.449 --> 00:03:21.618
I don't know if it's about
these two or about the kid.

18
00:03:23.020 --> 00:03:24.687
What kid?

19
00:03:24.721 --> 00:03:26.857
I thought he was dead
until he took a breath.

20
00:03:26.891 --> 00:03:28.558
The paramedics have him.

21
00:03:29.726 --> 00:03:32.063
Hey. I hear you're
leaving the department.

22
00:03:32.096 --> 00:03:33.297
Is that true. Joe?

23
00:03:34.365 --> 00:03:35.698
Yeah.

24
00:03:37.101 --> 00:03:39.003
Man. you're not even 50.

25
00:03:40.371 --> 00:03:42.339
What. you hit
the lottery or something?

26
00:03:44.308 --> 00:03:46.010
Sometimes you just know.

27
00:03:46.043 --> 00:03:48.012
You should...
should go canvass.

28
00:04:02.692 --> 00:04:04.727
[siren wailing]

29
00:04:10.301 --> 00:04:12.303
[reporter on TV] <i>A man
in Larchmont took his dog</i>

30
00:04:12.336 --> 00:04:15.805
<i>on their normal morning stroll.
something he'd done for years.</i>

31
00:04:15.839 --> 00:04:18.042
<i>Only this time he found
himself being drawn into</i>

32
00:04:18.075 --> 00:04:21.112
<i>what can only be called
a very gruesome scene.</i>

33
00:04:21.145 --> 00:04:23.080
<i>On his walk.
the man noticed</i>

34
00:04:23.114 --> 00:04:25.748
<i>that Nicholas and Wendy
Gervich's front door</i>

35
00:04:25.782 --> 00:04:27.384
<i>was left partially open.</i>

36
00:04:27.418 --> 00:04:29.353
<i>Being friends
with the owners of the home.</i>

37
00:04:29.386 --> 00:04:31.155
<i>he decided to investigate.</i>

38
00:04:31.188 --> 00:04:33.756
<i>Once inside.
he found two people murdered</i>

39
00:04:33.790 --> 00:04:36.060
<i>and their son
brutally beaten.</i>

40
00:04:36.093 --> 00:04:37.895
- Damn shame.
- <i>While we can only speculate</i>

41
00:04:37.928 --> 00:04:40.064
<i>what really happened
in this house last night...</i>

42
00:04:40.097 --> 00:04:41.764
- [Drew] San Diego?
- No.

43
00:04:43.033 --> 00:04:44.268
Heard about that.

44
00:04:44.969 --> 00:04:47.138
- Damn shame.
- That's what I said.

45
00:04:47.171 --> 00:04:48.705
[chuckling]

46
00:04:51.708 --> 00:04:53.710
You still back there
watching the game?

47
00:04:53.743 --> 00:04:57.114
Well. the Padres lost.
I got caught watching the news.

48
00:04:57.148 --> 00:05:00.417
- Lloyd. you know nothing good comes from the news.
- [Lloyd] That's right.

49
00:05:00.451 --> 00:05:02.987
- I have to get this ready before Marcus gets here.
- [doorbell rings]

50
00:05:03.020 --> 00:05:05.055
- [door opens]
- [Anthony] Hey. hey. hey.

51
00:05:05.089 --> 00:05:07.858
- Hey. family.
- Ha! What's up. Drew?

52
00:05:07.892 --> 00:05:09.960
- [Drew] What's going on?
- Look at you. boy. You looking good.

53
00:05:09.994 --> 00:05:12.229
- No. no. you looking better.
- Okay. I'll take that.

54
00:05:12.263 --> 00:05:14.064
- What's up. gorgeous?
- [Tisha] Hey. bro.

55
00:05:14.098 --> 00:05:15.966
- Come here. Come on. now.
- Which way we gonna go?

56
00:05:16.000 --> 00:05:18.169
- How are you doing?
- [Drew] Good to see you.

57
00:05:18.202 --> 00:05:22.039
Pastor. I'm sure I can find that
scripture for you no problem. Okay?

58
00:05:22.072 --> 00:05:23.274
All right. bye.

59
00:05:24.275 --> 00:05:26.410
[all chattering]

60
00:05:26.443 --> 00:05:28.946
- Hey. how are you doing?
- Who were you talking to. the pastor?

61
00:05:28.979 --> 00:05:30.281
- Apparently.
- [Drew] What's up. bro?

62
00:05:30.314 --> 00:05:31.848
What's up. man?
What's up. Dad?

63
00:05:31.882 --> 00:05:33.050
- Hey. son.
- How you feeling?

64
00:05:33.083 --> 00:05:34.251
I'm all right.

65
00:05:34.285 --> 00:05:35.818
- Hey. baby.
- What's up. Mom?

66
00:05:35.853 --> 00:05:37.021
- I'm good.
- Hey. Terry.

67
00:05:37.054 --> 00:05:38.389
[Terry]
The food looks good.

68
00:05:38.422 --> 00:05:40.124
- What's up. Tisha?
- How are you?

69
00:05:40.157 --> 00:05:42.725
Lloyd. Marcus is gonna be
late for his own party.

70
00:05:42.759 --> 00:05:44.761
Has anybody
talked to Marcus?

71
00:05:44.794 --> 00:05:46.297
[Anne] Four years sober.

72
00:05:48.798 --> 00:05:51.001
I just keep waiting
for it to slip away.

73
00:05:52.403 --> 00:05:55.139
- [phone buzzing]
- But I keep reminding myself

74
00:05:55.172 --> 00:05:56.839
to stay focused

75
00:05:56.874 --> 00:05:58.242
on my greatest good.

76
00:05:59.276 --> 00:06:01.045
[people clapping]

77
00:06:06.417 --> 00:06:09.186
Marcus. would you like
to join in?

78
00:06:11.522 --> 00:06:13.424
Uh. sure.

79
00:06:15.059 --> 00:06:17.895
You all know I've had
trouble staying sober.

80
00:06:17.928 --> 00:06:19.063
Um...

81
00:06:20.531 --> 00:06:23.100
but I think I finally found
a reason to pull through.

82
00:06:23.534 --> 00:06:25.302
That's good.
Marcus.

83
00:06:25.336 --> 00:06:27.238
Would you care to let
us know the reason?

84
00:06:28.372 --> 00:06:30.307
- I got a new job.
- Oh.

85
00:06:30.341 --> 00:06:32.209
Yeah. my dad got me
this great new job.

86
00:06:32.243 --> 00:06:34.311
I'm gonna be driving buses
for the city.

87
00:06:35.845 --> 00:06:37.514
So hopefully.
I'll get my shit together.

88
00:06:37.548 --> 00:06:39.083
[chuckles]

89
00:06:44.421 --> 00:06:46.290
[line ringing]

90
00:06:50.561 --> 00:06:53.430
Uh. hey. Wanda.
it's Eva returning your call.

91
00:06:55.499 --> 00:06:56.934
Mm-hmm.

92
00:06:58.068 --> 00:06:59.336
Mm-hmm.

93
00:07:00.471 --> 00:07:02.106
Yeah. Hey.

94
00:07:02.139 --> 00:07:03.407
[door closes]

95
00:07:03.440 --> 00:07:06.277
Yo. Marcus.
Hey. where were you. man?

96
00:07:08.212 --> 00:07:10.948
- You know.
- Oh. that's right. All right. Got you.

97
00:07:10.981 --> 00:07:13.117
Eva. Hey. how you doing?

98
00:07:13.150 --> 00:07:15.853
- Uh. Tisha's in here waiting on you.
- [Eva] Got to go.

99
00:07:15.886 --> 00:07:17.855
- Okay.
- [Anthony] She's a nurse over at the Cathedral.

100
00:07:17.888 --> 00:07:20.257
Tish and she are good friends.
They're good friends together.

101
00:07:20.291 --> 00:07:22.159
- Mm-hmm.
- Eva. this is Marcus.

102
00:07:22.192 --> 00:07:23.594
Marcus. this is Eva.

103
00:07:23.627 --> 00:07:25.362
- Hi.
- Hey.

104
00:07:27.898 --> 00:07:31.201
No. no. this is the brother. This is the
brother that Tish was telling you about.

105
00:07:32.569 --> 00:07:36.307
Oh. uh. Tisha just said
I was here for dinner.

106
00:07:38.042 --> 00:07:40.144
- She did?
- Mm-hmm.

107
00:07:40.177 --> 00:07:43.013
Okay. come on in. Food...
Food's ready. It's hot.

108
00:07:43.047 --> 00:07:44.415
It's ready.

109
00:07:44.448 --> 00:07:46.150
- Now. Eva?
- Mm-hmm?

110
00:07:46.183 --> 00:07:48.018
Can you do me a favor?
Can you not tell Tish

111
00:07:48.052 --> 00:07:50.020
about this moment
that we just had out here?

112
00:07:50.054 --> 00:07:51.955
Oh. I'm gonna get you
in trouble.

113
00:07:51.989 --> 00:07:53.324
[chuckles]

114
00:08:02.900 --> 00:08:04.168
Thank you.

115
00:08:05.202 --> 00:08:07.471
[all laughing. chattering]

116
00:08:29.126 --> 00:08:31.495
[laughing. chattering continues]

117
00:08:45.142 --> 00:08:47.411
- She's really nice.
- [sports chatter on TV]

118
00:08:47.444 --> 00:08:51.448
And Tish told me that she
invited her here to meet you.

119
00:08:51.482 --> 00:08:56.954
But yet here you are in a room
full of men that you already know.

120
00:08:56.987 --> 00:09:00.391
Uh. can y'all tell your
mother to mind her business?

121
00:09:00.424 --> 00:09:04.061
Uh. excuse me. son.
You are my business.

122
00:09:04.094 --> 00:09:05.362
You're my baby.

123
00:09:07.631 --> 00:09:10.067
So does anybody want to
help with the dishes?

124
00:09:11.402 --> 00:09:13.537
Nobody? Really?

125
00:09:14.238 --> 00:09:15.372
Pop?

126
00:09:16.507 --> 00:09:17.674
Pop?

127
00:09:19.610 --> 00:09:22.045
- [Lloyd] Hey. Marcus.
- Yeah?

128
00:09:22.079 --> 00:09:24.548
Would you please get
your old daddy a beer?

129
00:09:24.581 --> 00:09:26.417
Oh. my goodness.
you too. Pop?

130
00:09:26.450 --> 00:09:29.420
Yeah. Marcus.
Get your dad a beer.

131
00:09:29.453 --> 00:09:31.955
[chattering]

132
00:09:31.989 --> 00:09:33.223
- [Lloyd] Be cool.
- [chuckles]

133
00:09:34.057 --> 00:09:35.292
What's up. y'all?

134
00:09:35.325 --> 00:09:36.360
Hey.

135
00:09:36.994 --> 00:09:40.097
[Marcus] Oh. man.
that food was good.

136
00:09:40.130 --> 00:09:41.365
[clears throat]

137
00:09:45.169 --> 00:09:48.205
You know what? Let me go see if I
can find some more dishes. okay?

138
00:09:49.640 --> 00:09:50.674
[Eva] Mm-hmm.

139
00:09:57.314 --> 00:09:59.116
You have a good time
tonight?

140
00:09:59.149 --> 00:10:00.284
Yeah. I did.

141
00:10:01.318 --> 00:10:04.054
- My mama can burn.
- Mm-hmm.

142
00:10:04.087 --> 00:10:05.122
[Marcus] You?

143
00:10:10.194 --> 00:10:13.497
So you're starting
a new job tomorrow.

144
00:10:14.231 --> 00:10:15.265
You nervous?

145
00:10:16.166 --> 00:10:17.534
Little bit. yeah.

146
00:10:17.568 --> 00:10:19.069
Some advice?

147
00:10:20.571 --> 00:10:23.407
Try not to think
about failing.

148
00:10:23.440 --> 00:10:25.342
Just let things flow.

149
00:10:28.579 --> 00:10:30.113
Hey. yo. Terry.

150
00:10:30.147 --> 00:10:31.315
[Terry] Huh?

151
00:10:31.348 --> 00:10:32.649
Terry!

152
00:10:32.683 --> 00:10:34.618
[Terry]
Coming. coming. coming. [grunts]

153
00:10:36.453 --> 00:10:40.724
Hey. give that to Pop.
I'm. uh. gonna help out with the dishes.

154
00:10:41.825 --> 00:10:43.527
You don't do dishes.

155
00:10:43.560 --> 00:10:46.497
Dry-snitching.
You must be the baby brother.

156
00:10:47.264 --> 00:10:48.398
I like her.

157
00:10:50.434 --> 00:10:52.236
- Oh. yeah. I'm...
- [Eva chuckles]

158
00:10:54.705 --> 00:10:56.507
[both clear throat]

159
00:10:58.509 --> 00:11:00.344
You know. for the record.

160
00:11:00.377 --> 00:11:04.314
I don't have anything to do
with the whole set-up thing.

161
00:11:04.348 --> 00:11:07.217
- Blind date...
- I can tell.

162
00:11:07.251 --> 00:11:10.287
- You've been avoiding me all night.
- No. I wasn't avoiding you.

163
00:11:10.320 --> 00:11:12.556
I just didn't want you
to feel pressured.

164
00:11:12.589 --> 00:11:14.124
I appreciate that.

165
00:11:15.792 --> 00:11:17.394
That's the worst feeling.

166
00:11:18.328 --> 00:11:19.763
You being pressured?

167
00:11:19.796 --> 00:11:22.299
Yeah. I feel like that
all the time.

168
00:11:23.467 --> 00:11:24.701
By who?

169
00:11:27.371 --> 00:11:28.472
Me.

170
00:11:34.311 --> 00:11:38.415
Tish. um. had a lot of nice
things to say about you.

171
00:11:39.550 --> 00:11:41.485
I should have figured
something was up.

172
00:11:42.319 --> 00:11:43.820
Tish talks a lot.

173
00:11:44.721 --> 00:11:45.857
She does.

174
00:11:45.890 --> 00:11:48.191
[both laugh]

175
00:11:49.861 --> 00:11:51.295
Yeah.

176
00:11:51.328 --> 00:11:53.630
Did Tish tell you
anything about me?

177
00:11:55.900 --> 00:12:01.672
I mean. no. Like I said.
you were a complete surprise.

178
00:12:04.641 --> 00:12:06.677
Did she tell you
anything about me?

179
00:12:09.713 --> 00:12:13.717
Life's been hard for you.
but you keep trying.

180
00:12:18.455 --> 00:12:21.358
I lost my two oldest brothers
to LA life.

181
00:12:22.225 --> 00:12:25.295
One to drugs.
the other to gang violence.

182
00:12:25.329 --> 00:12:27.130
- I'm sorry to hear that.
- Mmm.

183
00:12:29.266 --> 00:12:32.169
I kind of gave up on brothers

184
00:12:32.202 --> 00:12:34.171
who were trying to get
themselves together.

185
00:12:34.204 --> 00:12:38.475
until I realized we're all
trying to get ourselves together.

186
00:12:42.179 --> 00:12:44.114
I haven't dated in a while.

187
00:12:44.949 --> 00:12:46.750
It's hard when you nurse.

188
00:12:46.783 --> 00:12:49.887
and I want to find
a good brother.

189
00:12:52.289 --> 00:12:54.558
And now I sound desperate.

190
00:12:55.325 --> 00:12:57.594
- So now I'm shutting up. [chuckles]
- No. you...

191
00:12:57.628 --> 00:12:59.229
[chuckles]

192
00:13:05.302 --> 00:13:06.770
Let me ask you something.

193
00:13:08.639 --> 00:13:11.341
Are you always this honest?

194
00:13:11.375 --> 00:13:14.211
Surprises are for birthdays
and Christmas.

195
00:13:15.245 --> 00:13:17.781
Not when you're trying
to get to know someone.

196
00:13:21.284 --> 00:13:22.452
Hmm.

197
00:13:25.389 --> 00:13:26.790
Go.

198
00:13:28.725 --> 00:13:31.863
So. uh.
I guess this is good night.

199
00:13:32.629 --> 00:13:35.832
Or this is when you
ask me for my number.

200
00:13:36.566 --> 00:13:38.903
555-6433.

201
00:13:38.936 --> 00:13:40.905
Tish gave it to me
when we were...

202
00:13:40.938 --> 00:13:43.607
She texted it to me when
we were cleaning up the kitchen.

203
00:13:43.640 --> 00:13:44.976
Of course she did.

204
00:13:45.009 --> 00:13:47.444
- Yeah. Told you she got a big mouth.
- Yup.

205
00:13:49.312 --> 00:13:50.614
You should use it.

206
00:13:51.481 --> 00:13:52.616
Yes. ma'am.

207
00:13:54.351 --> 00:13:56.386
- I should go. Mm-hmm.
- All right.

208
00:13:56.420 --> 00:13:57.788
- Hey. get home safe.
- I will.

209
00:13:57.821 --> 00:13:58.956
- Bye-bye.
- Good night.

210
00:13:58.990 --> 00:14:00.223
Good night.

211
00:14:07.631 --> 00:14:08.832
[door opens]

212
00:14:13.403 --> 00:14:14.838
I can drive. man.

213
00:14:14.872 --> 00:14:16.773
Let me drive.
You're drunk off your ass.

214
00:14:16.807 --> 00:14:18.442
- I'm gonna get him home.
- You're gonna take him?

215
00:14:18.475 --> 00:14:20.277
Yup. I got it.
I got it. Pop.

216
00:14:20.310 --> 00:14:22.412
No. no. you're going
with Marcus.

217
00:14:22.446 --> 00:14:24.347
- Here you go.
- All right then. you got him?

218
00:14:24.381 --> 00:14:26.249
- Yup. I got him.
- Love y'all.

219
00:14:26.283 --> 00:14:28.351
It ain't cool getting drunk
like that in front of Marcus.

220
00:14:28.385 --> 00:14:30.287
- All right. I love you. Pop.
- It's all good.

221
00:14:30.320 --> 00:14:32.924
- Mm-hmm. you too.
- Goddamn.

222
00:14:32.957 --> 00:14:34.658
Wait. wait.
wait. wait.

223
00:14:34.691 --> 00:14:37.294
Don't throw up
on my walkway.

224
00:14:37.327 --> 00:14:38.528
Uh-uh. uh-uh.

225
00:14:41.331 --> 00:14:42.900
- I love you. man.
- Hey. I love you too.

226
00:14:51.075 --> 00:14:52.809
You're not here much.
are you?

227
00:14:52.843 --> 00:14:54.511
[sighs]

228
00:14:56.981 --> 00:14:58.715
I stay at Rhea's
most of the time.

229
00:15:00.350 --> 00:15:02.352
She won't stay here.

230
00:15:02.385 --> 00:15:04.321
You should try cleaning up
every now and then.

231
00:15:04.354 --> 00:15:08.558
You feeling good
about yourself. huh? [grunts]

232
00:15:09.392 --> 00:15:10.995
- Yeah. I guess.
- Hmm.

233
00:15:13.030 --> 00:15:16.733
You're sober.
You got a job.

234
00:15:17.834 --> 00:15:19.636
Shit is looking up. man.

235
00:15:19.669 --> 00:15:22.472
- You're sounding jealous.
- [chuckles]

236
00:15:22.506 --> 00:15:26.878
I guess Mama praying to Jesus
and his cousins finally worked.

237
00:15:28.678 --> 00:15:30.313
You know. you like a cat.

238
00:15:31.082 --> 00:15:32.884
Black cat. [chuckles]

239
00:15:34.886 --> 00:15:36.653
You got nine goddamn lives.

240
00:15:36.686 --> 00:15:37.889
You ain't happy for me?

241
00:15:37.922 --> 00:15:39.289
Marcus. sit down.

242
00:15:39.857 --> 00:15:42.492
I think if I keep looking up.
I'ma throw up.

243
00:15:51.135 --> 00:15:52.769
You know...

244
00:15:57.108 --> 00:15:59.576
it's like you and I
traded places.

245
00:16:01.112 --> 00:16:02.646
I lost my job. man.

246
00:16:02.679 --> 00:16:05.950
The gas company?
That job's for life.

247
00:16:07.717 --> 00:16:09.854
Corporate bullshit.

248
