491
00:31:51.795 --> 00:31:53.530
- You sure?
- Yeah.

492
00:31:55.032 --> 00:31:56.433
How are you and Eva?

493
00:31:58.002 --> 00:31:59.669
- Eva's good.
- Eva's good?

494
00:31:59.703 --> 00:32:01.738
- Yeah.
- [laughing]

495
00:32:01.772 --> 00:32:04.541
Well. y'all two should come by
the crib sometime for some dinner.

496
00:32:04.574 --> 00:32:05.910
Just us and the ladies.

497
00:32:05.943 --> 00:32:07.844
- We could do that.
- All right.

498
00:32:07.879 --> 00:32:09.513
- All right. man.
- All right. man. Love you.

499
00:32:09.546 --> 00:32:10.580
Love you too. bro.

500
00:32:14.051 --> 00:32:15.519
[music playing on radio]

501
00:32:17.855 --> 00:32:18.956
[music stops]

502
00:32:21.525 --> 00:32:22.659
[car door opens]

503
00:32:23.493 --> 00:32:24.728
What's up. D?

504
00:32:24.761 --> 00:32:25.829
What up?

505
00:32:33.905 --> 00:32:35.639
So you think
that was a smart move?

506
00:32:35.672 --> 00:32:37.541
Asking me if shit is bad

507
00:32:37.574 --> 00:32:40.343
around niggas that you think
may have it bad for me?

508
00:32:40.377 --> 00:32:42.612
I need you to know
how serious this is.

509
00:32:42.646 --> 00:32:45.116
Look. man. I know you being sober
and all gave you a conscience...

510
00:32:45.149 --> 00:32:48.518
Going to jail gave me a conscience.
Being sober means I live with it.

511
00:32:49.419 --> 00:32:53.623
Drew. just go online
and pull up the news segment.

512
00:32:53.657 --> 00:32:56.426
If Stacy did what you said.
Marcus.

513
00:32:56.459 --> 00:32:58.495
remember this is Al and Stacy
that we talking about.

514
00:32:58.528 --> 00:33:00.564
- I know.
- If I give those cards back.

515
00:33:00.597 --> 00:33:02.833
they're gonna think
that I can't be trusted.

516
00:33:02.867 --> 00:33:03.901
Then what?

517
00:33:06.904 --> 00:33:08.705
You remember
what happened to Bob Cat?

518
00:33:09.706 --> 00:33:11.108
They never found him.

519
00:33:12.409 --> 00:33:14.011
If you think they did that.

520
00:33:14.644 --> 00:33:16.580
then let the police
deal with it.

521
00:33:17.281 --> 00:33:19.583
Don't fuck around and get us
caught up in something. man?

522
00:33:20.151 --> 00:33:21.418
All right?

523
00:33:23.486 --> 00:33:24.621
Come on. man. [chuckles]

524
00:33:25.722 --> 00:33:26.756
Mm-hmm.

525
00:33:29.759 --> 00:33:31.128
You look good. bro.

526
00:33:31.162 --> 00:33:32.864
- You still can't play ball.
- [chuckles]

527
00:33:32.897 --> 00:33:35.867
So your girl
dresses you now. huh? [chuckles]

528
00:33:35.900 --> 00:33:38.602
[Vernon] <i>And what I've heard from
every neighbor that we've spoken to.</i>

529
00:33:38.635 --> 00:33:40.071
<i>is that this was
a loving family.</i>

530
00:33:40.104 --> 00:33:42.405
A family that would do
whatever they could

531
00:33:42.439 --> 00:33:46.509
to help people in need. And they did
not deserve this tragic. brutal end.

532
00:33:46.543 --> 00:33:50.882
[Rick] <i>Any idea if the police
are close on any suspects?</i>

533
00:33:50.915 --> 00:33:52.616
[Vernon]
<i>That's the sad part. Rick.</i>

534
00:33:52.649 --> 00:33:54.852
There was no trace
of evidence left behind.

535
00:33:54.886 --> 00:33:58.788
which makes the police think these
were cold. calculated invaders

536
00:33:58.822 --> 00:34:01.025
who may have done this before.

537
00:34:01.058 --> 00:34:03.961
There's hope that someone
will stop these criminals

538
00:34:03.995 --> 00:34:05.662
before they kill again.

539
00:34:05.695 --> 00:34:08.065
Reporting live.
I'm Vernon Nelson for KRAC.

540
00:34:08.099 --> 00:34:11.135
God. what a terrible
position to be put in.

541
00:34:12.469 --> 00:34:13.670
To snitch?

542
00:34:14.238 --> 00:34:15.639
Yeah.

543
00:34:17.008 --> 00:34:18.475
Would you be good
knowing someone

544
00:34:18.508 --> 00:34:19.776
who might have
been involved?

545
00:34:24.614 --> 00:34:27.450
I hope I ain't ever
put in that situation.

546
00:34:32.489 --> 00:34:33.690
Would you?

547
00:35:40.224 --> 00:35:45.729
How you doing? Um. I have information
on the Gervich home invasion.

548
00:36:02.313 --> 00:36:04.915
[no audible dialogue]

549
00:36:23.234 --> 00:36:26.803
Tell Nate I'm gonna let them sit for the
night. Give them something to think about.

550
00:36:26.836 --> 00:36:29.006
- Copy that.
- [engine starts]

551
00:36:32.609 --> 00:36:34.811
[siren wailing]

552
00:36:34.844 --> 00:36:36.981
[helicopter whirring]

553
00:36:37.415 --> 00:36:39.616
[Marcus] Hey. man.

554
00:36:39.649 --> 00:36:41.818
Leave that other team alone.
the purple and gold.

555
00:36:41.852 --> 00:36:43.620
All right?
That's the way.

556
00:36:45.156 --> 00:36:46.891
[phone buzzing]

557
00:36:49.626 --> 00:36:51.128
Hey. what up. D?

558
00:36:51.162 --> 00:36:53.030
[Drew]
<i>Yo. Al and Stacy got arrested.</i>

559
00:36:53.630 --> 00:36:56.766
- Really?
- <i>I need to know that they ain't being taken in</i>

560
00:36:56.800 --> 00:36:58.002
<i>because of you.</i>

561
00:36:58.869 --> 00:37:02.873
Me? You said I was
overreacting. so I fell back.

562
00:37:04.741 --> 00:37:05.775
<i>All right.</i>

563
00:37:07.878 --> 00:37:09.046
All right. man.

564
00:37:18.655 --> 00:37:21.358
Why'd you keep me here overnight.
Officer Blue Over Black?

565
00:37:21.392 --> 00:37:22.826
So why'd you keep me overnight?

566
00:37:23.294 --> 00:37:25.863
You ever watch
reality cop shows on TV?

567
00:37:25.896 --> 00:37:27.730
[sighs. blows raspberry]

568
00:37:28.299 --> 00:37:30.633
We separate you.
Then we ask questions.

569
00:37:30.667 --> 00:37:32.735
Then we shake you up
to see if the answers jibe.

570
00:37:32.769 --> 00:37:35.039
At least you started
with the truth.

571
00:37:35.873 --> 00:37:37.174
Good. your turn.

572
00:37:37.807 --> 00:37:41.011
I want you to think back
maybe three months ago.

573
00:37:41.545 --> 00:37:43.646
Tell me your whereabouts
three months ago

574
00:37:43.680 --> 00:37:46.984
- on the night of the 16th.
- Hmm.

575
00:37:48.018 --> 00:37:49.186
My guess. Chops.

576
00:37:49.220 --> 00:37:50.620
Chops.

577
00:37:51.188 --> 00:37:53.858
You know.
try to have a few drinks.

578
00:37:53.891 --> 00:37:55.126
hang out with the ladies.

579
00:37:55.893 --> 00:37:58.095
But I do remember
it was crowded that night.

580
00:37:58.129 --> 00:38:02.933
So we. um. probably
took off maybe 11:30?

581
00:38:02.967 --> 00:38:05.202
Actually. maybe like
11:00. 11:15?

582
00:38:06.270 --> 00:38:07.737
You were in a club
all night?

583
00:38:07.770 --> 00:38:09.273
[Al] In and out. You know.

584
00:38:09.306 --> 00:38:11.375
some of the ladies
like to hang out outside.

585
00:38:11.408 --> 00:38:13.277
Do all their. like.
videos and shit.

586
00:38:13.310 --> 00:38:16.046
What'd you think
a handsome cat gonna do?

587
00:38:16.080 --> 00:38:18.282
I'ma be in and out. [laughs]

588
00:38:18.315 --> 00:38:19.950
[Al] Um.
but I don't know. man.

589
00:38:19.984 --> 00:38:22.153
I don't really remember.
It was a while ago.

590
00:38:22.186 --> 00:38:24.021
Three months?

591
00:38:24.054 --> 00:38:25.788
Had a few drinks...

592
00:38:25.822 --> 00:38:28.825
[Al] And we usually
go as a crew.

593
00:38:28.859 --> 00:38:30.995
And we usually run into
a bunch of people we know.

594
00:38:31.028 --> 00:38:33.397
We always bump
into folks that we know.

595
00:38:33.430 --> 00:38:37.268
And for some reason. we didn't bump
into anybody we know that night.

596
00:38:37.301 --> 00:38:38.903
- [Al] Nobody was there.
- Hmm.

597
00:38:38.936 --> 00:38:41.305
So we bounced early.
I had to work.

598
00:38:41.338 --> 00:38:43.908
I had to start cutting early
the next morning.

599
00:38:43.941 --> 00:38:46.243
Got out of there like...
what did I say before?

600
00:38:46.277 --> 00:38:48.078
11:30. 11:15?
Something like that.

601
00:38:51.949 --> 00:38:53.851
You work at
Dillaman's Department Store.

602
00:38:54.952 --> 00:38:56.353
What gave it away?

603
00:38:56.387 --> 00:38:59.957
Mr. Gervich ate
at Dillaman's Café a lot.

604
00:38:59.990 --> 00:39:03.793
He valeted when he did.
He left his tickets in his door panel.

605
00:39:05.362 --> 00:39:06.864
I don't know that. man.

606
00:39:07.498 --> 00:39:10.501
I don't go to Al's job.
I got my own shit.

607
00:39:10.534 --> 00:39:16.240
Look. man. A lot of people
eat lunch at Dillaman's.

608
00:39:16.273 --> 00:39:19.009
Lunch time is a very busy time.

609
00:39:19.043 --> 00:39:24.148
And even if I did see that dude.
I wouldn't remember him.

610
00:39:24.714 --> 00:39:27.017
I see a lot of faces in there.

611
00:39:27.885 --> 00:39:29.253
So you don't know him?

612
00:39:29.752 --> 00:39:31.355
[Al] I don't know him.

613
00:39:31.922 --> 00:39:33.790
And you don't know me

614
00:39:33.823 --> 00:39:35.825
unless you been to Chops.

615
00:39:35.859 --> 00:39:38.362
[Joe] So it was just you and
Stacy at Chops that night?

616
00:39:38.395 --> 00:39:41.365
[Al] Nah. it was me. Stacy.
and Drew Cowans.

617
00:39:41.398 --> 00:39:44.101
He can vouch for us.
He's here. right?

618
00:39:44.134 --> 00:39:46.437
- [Anthony] Got it. Yeah.
- [Terry] Got it?

619
00:39:46.470 --> 00:39:49.306
[Lloyd] Hey. you guys wanna head
over to the Advent with me tonight?

620
00:39:49.340 --> 00:39:51.308
Hear what kind of lies
Andrew is gonna be telling?

621
00:39:53.510 --> 00:39:56.547
The worst ever.
The absolute worst.

622
00:39:56.580 --> 00:39:58.983
If it wasn't for him.
I'd have never met your mama.

623
00:39:59.016 --> 00:40:00.050
Really?

624
00:40:04.989 --> 00:40:06.523
You think Marcus
might wanna come?

625
00:40:06.557 --> 00:40:08.926
No. no. Marcus is
all cuddled up. Dad.

626
00:40:08.959 --> 00:40:10.261
- All cuddled up.
- Mmm.

627
00:40:10.294 --> 00:40:11.428
- He good.
- Yeah?

628
00:40:11.462 --> 00:40:13.130
- Yes. sir.
- Yes.

629
00:40:13.163 --> 00:40:15.499
Good. good. about time
he found some peace of mind.

630
00:40:15.532 --> 00:40:17.401
- [both] "Peace of mind."
- [knocking on door]

631
00:40:17.434 --> 00:40:18.768
- [laughing]
- Mm-hmm.

632
00:40:20.871 --> 00:40:22.573
Looking for Drew Cowans.

633
00:40:22.606 --> 00:40:26.010
Detective Joe McDonald. LAPD.

634
00:40:26.043 --> 00:40:27.844
I'm his father.

635
00:40:27.878 --> 00:40:29.280
Nice to meet you.

636
00:40:29.313 --> 00:40:31.081
Just need to ask him
a few questions

637
00:40:31.115 --> 00:40:33.884
about Al Edwards
and Stacy Griffin.

638
00:40:34.451 --> 00:40:37.988
- Why?
- And you are?

639
00:40:38.022 --> 00:40:40.024
I'm his older brother.
Why are you at this house?

640
00:40:40.057 --> 00:40:43.360
[Joe] This is the address he put
down for his. uh. former job.

641
00:40:44.261 --> 00:40:45.496
Former?

642
00:40:46.063 --> 00:40:47.865
He hasn't worked
in six months.

643
00:40:49.300 --> 00:40:51.201
[hip-hop playing in car]

644
00:40:56.473 --> 00:40:57.807
[Lloyd] That's my son.

645
00:40:58.909 --> 00:41:01.378
Yeah. but before you put
a hand on him.

646
00:41:01.412 --> 00:41:04.214
you need to tell me what your
gonna speak to him about.

647
00:41:04.248 --> 00:41:05.848
- All right.
- No. hey.

648
00:41:05.883 --> 00:41:07.918
- Hey.
- You need to tell me

649
00:41:07.951 --> 00:41:10.454
- what you gonna speak to him about.
- Daddy. what's going on?

650
00:41:10.487 --> 00:41:12.589
[Lloyd] Drew. these men
are here to talk to you.

651
00:41:12.623 --> 00:41:15.259
- Drew Cowans. you're under arrest.
- Under arrest?

652
00:41:15.292 --> 00:41:17.127
Your friends Al
and Stacy implicated you

653
00:41:17.161 --> 00:41:19.196
in an investigation
regarding a home invasion

654
00:41:19.229 --> 00:41:21.465
- that occurred about three months ago.
- A home invasion?

655
00:41:21.498 --> 00:41:23.634
What the fuck you talking about?
Get off me! Daddy!

656
00:41:23.667 --> 00:41:26.170
- [Lloyd] I got it. Don't worry.
- Daddy. I ain't do nothing!

657
00:41:26.203 --> 00:41:28.972
I know you didn't. What are you
talking about? A home invasion?

658
00:41:29.006 --> 00:41:31.342
- The Gervich family.
- The Gervich family. you mean

659
00:41:31.375 --> 00:41:33.544
that husband and wife
that got killed

660
00:41:33.577 --> 00:41:35.979
- and the little boy survived?
- [Joe] Yes. sir.

661
00:41:36.013 --> 00:41:38.215
My son didn't have
nothing to do with that.

662
00:41:38.248 --> 00:41:40.050
My son didn't have
anything to do with that!

663
00:41:40.084 --> 00:41:41.618
[officer] Calm down!

664
00:41:41.652 --> 00:41:43.420
I'll call your mother.
I'm going to call your...

665
00:41:43.454 --> 00:41:44.955
Dad. Dad!

666
00:41:44.988 --> 00:41:47.291
If you kill
my fucking daddy. I swear...

667
00:41:47.324 --> 00:41:49.059
I swear to fucking God!

668
00:41:49.093 --> 00:41:51.028
- Get off me. man!
- Get an ambulance here now.

669
00:41:51.061 --> 00:41:52.262
[Drew] Open the fucking door!

670
00:41:52.296 --> 00:41:53.464
[Joe]
Let him down. Put him down.

671
00:41:53.497 --> 00:41:54.598
Get the fuck
out of here. man.

672
00:41:59.303 --> 00:42:00.671
What happened?

673
00:42:00.704 --> 00:42:03.374
Cops came to the house
looking for Drew.

674
00:42:03.407 --> 00:42:05.008
It's about that murder.

675
00:42:05.042 --> 00:42:07.077
That. um.
that fucking home invasion.

676
00:42:07.111 --> 00:42:08.579
Drew's a suspect?

677
00:42:08.612 --> 00:42:10.214
[Terry]
It was Al and Stacy.

678
00:42:10.247 --> 00:42:11.582
They must have lied
about something

679
00:42:11.615 --> 00:42:13.283
that got Drew brought in.

680
00:42:13.317 --> 00:42:14.351
Drew's in custody.

681
00:42:16.387 --> 00:42:17.654
Where's Mama?

682
00:42:17.688 --> 00:42:19.390
She's in there with Daddy.

683
00:42:21.959 --> 00:42:23.927
Look. why don't you
be with your brothers?

684
00:42:23.961 --> 00:42:25.629
I'll check in with you
later. okay?

685
00:42:30.734 --> 00:42:34.671
Marcus. you know anything about how
Drew got caught up in all this shit?

686
00:42:37.741 --> 00:42:39.710
Hanging with Al and Stacy.

687
00:42:39.743 --> 00:42:41.512
Hanging with someone
isn't a good enough reason

688
00:42:41.545 --> 00:42:43.213
- to bring him in for murder. Marcus.
- Okay.

689
00:42:43.247 --> 00:42:44.948
Watch it. we're here for Dad.

690
00:42:44.982 --> 00:42:46.450
- It's Drew.
- Look. look.

691
00:42:47.017 --> 00:42:49.319
Look. why don't you all
both go home. get some sleep.

692
00:42:49.353 --> 00:42:51.221
I'll stay with Mama
the rest of the night.

693
00:42:51.255 --> 00:42:53.457
- Are you sure?
- I'll let you know if anything changes.

694
00:42:53.490 --> 00:42:56.560
- Bro. I can stay here with you.
- No. I got it. Get some rest.

695
00:42:59.129 --> 00:43:00.330
Love you too.

696
00:43:02.299 --> 00:43:04.034
[whispering indistinctly]

697
00:43:18.115 --> 00:43:19.683
[monitor beeping]

698
00:43:42.773 --> 00:43:44.641
[beeping continues]

699
00:43:49.213 --> 00:43:51.081
Hey. boy.

700
00:43:51.114 --> 00:43:52.316
Hey. Pop.

701
00:43:52.349 --> 00:43:54.218
How you feeling?

702
00:43:54.718 --> 00:43:59.089
Yeah. had my ticker attack.

703
00:43:59.623 --> 00:44:01.024
[chuckles]

704
00:44:01.692 --> 00:44:03.794
It's funny how

705
00:44:03.827 --> 00:44:07.364
all the beating up my body took

706
00:44:07.397 --> 00:44:11.068
when I was working
at the post office...

707
00:44:12.536 --> 00:44:15.038
never thought
that I'd get laid out

708
00:44:15.072 --> 00:44:17.207
just 'cause a policeman
come to the door.

709
00:44:17.241 --> 00:44:20.410
Hey. man.
What you gonna do?

710
00:44:20.444 --> 00:44:22.679
- You just getting old.
- Ain't nobody old.

711
00:44:22.713 --> 00:44:24.414
I don't know what
you're talking about.

712
00:44:24.448 --> 00:44:27.217
[chuckles]
Where's your mama at?

713
00:44:28.452 --> 00:44:30.187
She's right over there
sleeping.

714
00:44:30.220 --> 00:44:31.488
[Della] No. I ain't.

715
00:44:32.389 --> 00:44:34.224
I can hear you fools.

716
00:44:34.258 --> 00:44:35.292
[grunts]

717
00:44:36.493 --> 00:44:39.563
So y'all hear. uh.
anything about Drew?

718
00:44:40.865 --> 00:44:42.666
No. ma'am. not yet.

719
00:44:46.203 --> 00:44:50.541
"Della. I ain't gonna let
nothing stress me out."

720
00:44:51.508 --> 00:44:53.443
You old lying ass.

721
00:44:53.477 --> 00:44:55.145
[both laughing]

722
00:44:56.647 --> 00:44:58.682
Look. you old man.
Since Marcus is here.

723
00:44:58.715 --> 00:45:01.418
- I'm gonna go stretch my legs. okay?
- Mm-hmm.

724
00:45:01.451 --> 00:45:03.387
[Della] All right.
[kisses]

725
00:45:03.420 --> 00:45:06.089
You behave yourself.
[chuckles]

726
00:45:06.123 --> 00:45:08.158
[footsteps departing]

727
00:45:10.227 --> 00:45:11.662
[door opens. closes]

728
00:45:11.695 --> 00:45:13.797
Just when we get you
out of trouble.

729
00:45:15.532 --> 00:45:17.634
hell's come knocking again.

730
00:45:17.668 --> 00:45:19.136
No. Pop.

731
00:45:21.906 --> 00:45:24.274
You ain't got to worry
about none of that.

732
00:45:25.075 --> 00:45:29.379
Yup. I think I'll just
rest my eyes a bit.

733
00:45:46.864 --> 00:45:49.232
- Hey. baby.
- Hey. Ma.

734
00:45:49.266 --> 00:45:51.368
So is he asking
for me already?

735
00:45:51.401 --> 00:45:53.337
- Nah. he fell asleep.
- [chuckles]

