- Hey!

1211
01:15:12.062 --> 01:15:15.399
[sighs] Those assholes
do not get to put their hand

1212
01:15:15.432 --> 01:15:17.134
on anybody in the Cowans family.

1213
01:15:17.167 --> 01:15:19.002
You understand me?

1214
01:15:19.603 --> 01:15:21.238
Do you fucking understand me?

1215
01:15:21.271 --> 01:15:22.506
Heard you. man.

1216
01:15:24.208 --> 01:15:25.676
So we gonna go talk to 'em.

1217
01:15:25.709 --> 01:15:28.145
- Let's go.
- No. we're not doing that.

1218
01:15:28.779 --> 01:15:31.448
- So now you're protecting them?
- No.

1219
01:15:31.482 --> 01:15:34.518
I'm trying to keep this shit from
getting crazier than what it already is.

1220
01:15:35.252 --> 01:15:37.921
I'ma go talk to 'em tomorrow.

1221
01:15:37.955 --> 01:15:40.391
Drew. you need to stay away
from both of 'em.

1222
01:15:41.091 --> 01:15:42.926
You right. T.

1223
01:15:42.960 --> 01:15:45.162
But do you think they really
gonna listen to you and Ant?

1224
01:15:45.195 --> 01:15:46.630
Come on. man.

1225
01:15:46.663 --> 01:15:48.966
- Let him go. T.
- After what they did to you.

1226
01:15:48.999 --> 01:15:51.068
- you wanna let him go down there?
- [Marcus] Let him go.

1227
01:15:51.635 --> 01:15:53.470
They're his friends. right?

1228
01:15:53.504 --> 01:15:57.274
So if they beat him up.
then we can go to the cops.

1229
01:15:57.307 --> 01:16:00.110
Then Drew can tell the police
everything they need to hear.

1230
01:16:01.011 --> 01:16:03.013
And this will all go away.

1231
01:16:03.046 --> 01:16:05.015
Look. I'ma call y'all

1232
01:16:05.048 --> 01:16:07.317
as soon as I talk to 'em
tomorrow. all right?

1233
01:16:07.351 --> 01:16:10.220
Drew. Drew. Drew. don't go around
there screwing with these guys.

1234
01:16:10.254 --> 01:16:13.424
Just go there. and tell 'em
to leave Marcus alone.

1235
01:16:13.457 --> 01:16:15.959
and put these motherfuckers
in your rearview. All right?

1236
01:16:15.993 --> 01:16:17.361
All right.

1237
01:16:22.166 --> 01:16:24.268
- Ant.
- [Marcus] Hey.

1238
01:16:29.573 --> 01:16:31.275
Don't do nothing stupid.

1239
01:16:42.319 --> 01:16:45.456
[whispers] Al told me
you killed that family.

1240
01:16:46.790 --> 01:16:48.358
[scoffs]

1241
01:16:50.594 --> 01:16:53.530
You of all people should know. Marcus.
that when shit is falling apart.

1242
01:16:53.564 --> 01:16:55.232
you don't want to go down alone.

1243
01:16:57.367 --> 01:16:58.669
In a week.

1244
01:16:59.636 --> 01:17:03.140
if they get desperate.
they're gonna say that your ass was there.

1245
01:17:08.745 --> 01:17:11.315
How does it feel
to be a fucking snitch?

1246
01:17:13.717 --> 01:17:15.519
Mind your fucking business.

1247
01:17:22.659 --> 01:17:26.296
[Stacy] I know. You ain't got to say it.
You ain't got to say it.

1248
01:17:26.330 --> 01:17:27.731
You told Marcus
I killed that family?

1249
01:17:27.764 --> 01:17:30.267
Yo. man. what the fuck!
Back the fuck up!

1250
01:17:31.268 --> 01:17:33.770
[laughs] Yeah. I did.

1251
01:17:33.804 --> 01:17:36.173
I was sick of his bullshit.

1252
01:17:36.206 --> 01:17:38.308
Boy. you better
calm your ass down.

1253
01:17:39.343 --> 01:17:40.777
Nigga. how stupid are you?

1254
01:17:41.645 --> 01:17:43.247
The cops interviewed us.

1255
01:17:43.280 --> 01:17:46.316
And we all told them
the same damn thing.

1256
01:17:46.350 --> 01:17:48.218
They don't have any evidence
to know that it was us.

1257
01:17:48.252 --> 01:17:50.254
If they had more.
they would have held us.

1258
01:17:51.655 --> 01:17:53.156
[Al] Oh. shit.

1259
01:17:55.192 --> 01:17:57.427
Maybe it wasn't your brother
who left the tip.

1260
01:17:59.396 --> 01:18:01.365
Maybe Drew here bitched up.

1261
01:18:02.165 --> 01:18:05.168
And now his ass is trying
to set us up.

1262
01:18:06.136 --> 01:18:09.606
Call the cops to keep himself clean.
Is that what you did?

1263
01:18:09.640 --> 01:18:11.708
And risk pissing you off?

1264
01:18:11.742 --> 01:18:14.578
And get my own self stuck up?
Come on. man.

1265
01:18:14.611 --> 01:18:18.749
Outside of Stacy. I ain't putting
anything past anyone. especially you.

1266
01:18:18.782 --> 01:18:21.151
I know what most of you two
crazy-asses gone and done

1267
01:18:21.184 --> 01:18:23.086
in the past few years.
and I ain't said shit.

1268
01:18:24.454 --> 01:18:27.558
So I don't know where you get off
thinking that you can't trust me?

1269
01:18:27.591 --> 01:18:29.560
Did your fucking dumbass
not hear me outside?

1270
01:18:29.593 --> 01:18:31.295
Man. who the fuck
are you talking to?

1271
01:18:31.328 --> 01:18:33.330
I don't fucking trust nobody!

1272
01:18:33.932 --> 01:18:37.701
And if it ain't you.
then someone's gonna be put down.

1273
01:18:38.870 --> 01:18:42.139
Whether it be
your junkie-ass brother.

1274
01:18:42.172 --> 01:18:44.775
who I heard was taking dicks
for bags.

1275
01:18:44.808 --> 01:18:49.813
- or whoever the fuck it is. I don't give a fuck.
- Calm the fuck down.

1276
01:18:55.752 --> 01:18:57.120
Drew.

1277
01:18:59.690 --> 01:19:04.261
If Marcus is behind this shit.
your ass got decisions. bro.

1278
01:19:05.362 --> 01:19:10.167
Because it's all three of us
against every-fucking-body

1279
01:19:10.200 --> 01:19:13.470
or it's you against me and Al.

1280
01:19:19.176 --> 01:19:22.446
Yeah. You think this is funny.
Okay. clap all you want.

1281
01:19:26.683 --> 01:19:28.352
Nobody fucks with my family.

1282
01:19:28.385 --> 01:19:29.486
[gunshot]

1283
01:19:33.223 --> 01:19:35.325
Whoa.
You gonna do me like that?

1284
01:19:35.359 --> 01:19:37.294
- Hmm.
- When all this shit is your fault?

1285
01:19:39.529 --> 01:19:41.164
Shut the fuck up!

1286
01:19:42.499 --> 01:19:44.735
Shut the fuck up! [echoes]

1287
01:19:44.768 --> 01:19:46.703
[car doors open. close]

1288
01:19:57.381 --> 01:19:58.715
Fuck!

1289
01:20:08.725 --> 01:20:10.494
[glass shattering]

1290
01:20:12.596 --> 01:20:15.432
Wait. What are you
guys doing in my house?

1291
01:20:20.938 --> 01:20:22.272
- Dad?
- Go.

1292
01:20:22.305 --> 01:20:23.774
Dad. Mom!

1293
01:20:24.341 --> 01:20:27.678
[Wendy] <i>Honey. what's wrong?
Nicholas. Kyle. God...</i>

1294
01:20:27.711 --> 01:20:29.914
[screaming]

1295
01:20:29.947 --> 01:20:31.515
[clattering]

1296
01:20:31.548 --> 01:20:33.250
- [Wendy screams]
- [Stacy] Stay the fuck down!

1297
01:20:38.455 --> 01:20:41.625
- [blows landing]
- [shouting]

1298
01:20:54.906 --> 01:20:58.408
- [Wendy screams. sobs]
- [gunshots]

1299
01:20:58.442 --> 01:21:00.544
[Stacy] <i>Yo.
what the fuck are you doing?</i>

1300
01:21:00.577 --> 01:21:02.479
[Drew] <i>Search the house.
I'll take care of the kid.</i>

1301
01:21:19.964 --> 01:21:22.699
So why didn't you tell us about
it when you first found out?

1302
01:21:24.969 --> 01:21:27.637
Honestly. I just had a hard time

1303
01:21:27.671 --> 01:21:29.606
wrapping my head around
what I knew.

1304
01:21:32.509 --> 01:21:34.745
[Terry] What you doing back here. man?
I thought you went home.

1305
01:21:35.913 --> 01:21:37.514
I. um...

1306
01:21:39.583 --> 01:21:40.852
I thought this through.

1307
01:21:42.086 --> 01:21:44.621
I shouldn't go talk
to Al and Stacy alone.

1308
01:21:45.890 --> 01:21:47.691
Maybe one of you can go with me.

1309
01:21:55.066 --> 01:21:57.001
You ain't gotta do this alone.

1310
01:22:00.004 --> 01:22:01.772
That's what we're here for.

1311
01:22:03.875 --> 01:22:05.509
Love you. man.

1312
01:22:07.410 --> 01:22:08.712
Always here for you.

1313
01:22:14.085 --> 01:22:16.486
[scoffs] Seriously.

1314
01:22:16.520 --> 01:22:19.389
- [laughing]
- [Terry] Y'all two. man.

1315
01:22:41.112 --> 01:22:44.949
Yeah. Marie says she'll take
over the next few days. Yeah.

1316
01:22:44.982 --> 01:22:46.550
Hey. uh. let me call you back.

1317
01:22:46.583 --> 01:22:47.952
All right. bye-bye.

1318
01:22:49.553 --> 01:22:52.957
- Good morning. my love.
- Good morning. sweetheart.

1319
01:22:52.990 --> 01:22:55.592
- How you feeling this morning?
- I'm good. I'm good.

1320
01:22:55.625 --> 01:22:58.829
You know. you should go in.
'cause that place falls apart without you.

1321
01:22:58.863 --> 01:23:01.832
No. we're not in tax season.
so we're good.

1322
01:23:01.866 --> 01:23:04.668
And who told you
to come in here without me. huh?

1323
01:23:04.701 --> 01:23:07.571
Look. I ain't no invalid.

1324
01:23:08.605 --> 01:23:11.943
Although. I did feel
a little tired

1325
01:23:11.976 --> 01:23:14.912
when I was trying to make it
over to turn on the radio.

1326
01:23:14.946 --> 01:23:17.547
Could you help me just
turn on the radio?

1327
01:23:17.581 --> 01:23:19.016
Oh. so now you need me. huh?

1328
01:23:19.050 --> 01:23:23.154
- Mr. I Ain't No Invalid.
- [both laughing]

1329
01:23:23.187 --> 01:23:26.057
You know. you ain't no badass just
'cause you're turning on the radio.

1330
01:23:26.090 --> 01:23:27.557
I'm the one
who had a heart attack.

1331
01:23:27.591 --> 01:23:28.860
- That you did.
- Yeah.

1332
01:23:28.893 --> 01:23:31.062
- You want some coffee?
- Huh? Yeah.

1333
01:23:31.095 --> 01:23:33.597
[newscaster] <i>...Stacy Griffin and his
friend Al Edwards were found murdered</i>

1334
01:23:33.630 --> 01:23:35.867
<i>this morning
at Stacy's barber shop.</i>

1335
01:23:35.900 --> 01:23:39.170
<i>Sources say police at the
scene seem to strongly believe</i>

1336
01:23:39.203 --> 01:23:41.771
<i>that it was
an armed robbery gone wrong.</i>

1337
01:23:41.805 --> 01:23:45.042
<i>...killed both men.
then proceeded to ransack the shop.</i>

1338
01:23:45.076 --> 01:23:46.911
<i>So far
there's been no witnesses.</i>

1339
01:23:46.944 --> 01:23:49.146
<i>Now. both men have been
in and out of trouble...</i>

1340
01:23:49.180 --> 01:23:51.381
[newscaster
continues indistinctly]

1341
01:24:06.964 --> 01:24:08.531
[phone buzzes]

1342
01:24:12.535 --> 01:24:14.471
[bell tolls]

1343
01:24:15.572 --> 01:24:17.041
[phone buzzes]

1344
01:24:17.975 --> 01:24:19.743
[phone buzzes]

1345
01:24:27.118 --> 01:24:28.518
Hello.

1346
01:24:34.791 --> 01:24:35.927
Hey.

1347
01:24:41.132 --> 01:24:43.700
Why'd you get involved
with this shit. Drew?

1348
01:24:54.078 --> 01:24:55.612
I got desperate.

1349
01:25:00.885 --> 01:25:02.186
And I was broke.

1350
01:25:07.258 --> 01:25:11.461
I saw how much Marcus was costing the
family. man. I didn't want to add to that.

1351
01:25:16.968 --> 01:25:18.035
It was dumb.

1352
01:25:22.806 --> 01:25:26.110
And you're lucky that
you weren't there last night.

1353
01:25:26.911 --> 01:25:27.945
[scoffs]

1354
01:25:29.880 --> 01:25:33.117
I think Marcus
did a really good thing

1355
01:25:33.150 --> 01:25:34.651
calling in that tip.

1356
01:25:35.552 --> 01:25:37.888
So... So don't be
too hard on him about that.

1357
01:25:37.922 --> 01:25:40.024
especially since he was trying
to protect you.

1358
01:25:44.761 --> 01:25:46.529
I won't. [sniffles]

1359
01:25:57.341 --> 01:26:00.710
- I'ma take a shower.
- Yeah. I'm gonna lay some clothes out for you. all right?

1360
01:26:00.744 --> 01:26:02.913
- All right.
- Hey. um. wait a minute.

1361
01:26:18.295 --> 01:26:19.930
[Drew sniffles]

1362
01:26:25.369 --> 01:26:28.738
[breathing heavily]

1363
01:26:31.375 --> 01:26:37.281
Listen. those dudes being dead
might not be such a bad thing. bro.

1364
01:26:38.883 --> 01:26:40.084
Okay?

1365
01:26:46.157 --> 01:26:47.590
[sniffles]

1366
01:26:49.692 --> 01:26:50.928
[exhales]

1367
01:26:56.400 --> 01:27:01.072
Well. at least what had happened
to you wasn't on the news. Drew.

1368
01:27:01.571 --> 01:27:05.042
- Yeah.
- No. it still don't stop them nosy-ass neighbors

1369
01:27:05.076 --> 01:27:06.277
- from talking.
- Mm-hmm.

1370
01:27:06.310 --> 01:27:08.045
You know the word had got out.

1371
01:27:08.079 --> 01:27:10.214
Mom. I don't care
what people saying now.

1372
01:27:10.247 --> 01:27:12.283
I got y'all.
If I didn't. I probably...

1373
01:27:12.316 --> 01:27:14.818
- Did anybody hear from Marcus?
- No.

1374
01:27:14.852 --> 01:27:16.686
What. he didn't call
none of y'all?

1375
01:27:17.288 --> 01:27:20.590
- Hey. you talk to him?
- I'll try him again. I'll try him again.

1376
01:27:22.826 --> 01:27:24.627
[line ringing]

1377
01:27:24.661 --> 01:27:26.263
[phone buzzing]

1378
01:27:30.733 --> 01:27:32.635
[buzzing continues]

1379
01:27:42.745 --> 01:27:47.084
You know. Marcus is probably still
mad that Al and Stacy attacked him.

1380
01:27:47.118 --> 01:27:49.819
Hmm. Yeah I would be. too.

1381
01:27:51.155 --> 01:27:53.891
What do you think really
happened with those dudes?

1382
01:27:55.292 --> 01:27:57.394
Well. I think
it's like Mama said.

1383
01:27:57.995 --> 01:28:00.131
Bad catches up with bad people.

1384
01:28:00.630 --> 01:28:02.832
I'm just glad
I ain't go talk to 'em.

1385
01:28:02.867 --> 01:28:03.934
Shit.

1386
01:28:04.468 --> 01:28:06.636
I might have been there
when they got shot.

1387
01:28:07.371 --> 01:28:10.975
Drew. baby. let me
talk to you for a minute.

1388
01:28:11.008 --> 01:28:12.309
Yes. ma'am.

1389
01:28:14.711 --> 01:28:15.845
What happened?

1390
01:28:17.348 --> 01:28:20.851
I told Mama and Daddy that that
lawyer might not be a bad idea.

1391
01:28:26.857 --> 01:28:28.058
Coming. Mama.

1392
01:28:32.997 --> 01:28:34.999
Terry. let me ask you this. bro.

1393
01:28:37.368 --> 01:28:41.405
Knowing what you know about what Drew
did. does that bother you?

1394
01:28:45.775 --> 01:28:46.843
A lot.

1395
01:28:49.846 --> 01:28:51.215
I pray on it every night.

1396
01:28:54.018 --> 01:28:55.818
But praying
doesn't change everything.

1397
01:29:00.157 --> 01:29:01.859
[Marcus] Hey. what's up. baby?

1398
01:29:04.295 --> 01:29:06.997
- Hey. Marcus.
- Hey. what's up? I miss you.

1399
01:29:10.167 --> 01:29:12.436
Marcus. have you been drinking?

1400
01:29:13.904 --> 01:29:16.273
Eva. Drew's homies.
Al and Stacy. they...

1401
01:29:17.007 --> 01:29:18.375
they got killed.

1402
01:29:18.409 --> 01:29:20.978
Police say it was a stickup
or some shit.

1403
01:29:29.286 --> 01:29:30.753
What do you say?

1404
01:29:31.355 --> 01:29:34.757
Some dirty niggas. E.
Could have been anybody.

1405
01:29:34.791 --> 01:29:37.428
But I know Drew was at the house
with Anthony when it happened.

1406
01:29:37.461 --> 01:29:39.029
I know that for sure.

1407
01:29:40.030 --> 01:29:42.266
- I just wanna talk to you. baby.
- Marcus. I don't have...

1408
01:29:42.299 --> 01:29:43.800
I wanna talk to you.

1409
01:29:43.833 --> 01:29:45.369
- I don't...
- I just gotta talk to you.

1410
01:29:47.037 --> 01:29:49.406
I gotta tell you something.
Okay?

1411
01:29:49.940 --> 01:29:52.775
And hopefully.
it will make you understand

1412
01:29:52.809 --> 01:29:54.811
why I tried to protect
my brother.

1413
01:29:54.844 --> 01:29:56.480
All right?

1414
01:29:56.513 --> 01:29:59.316
Tish. she ain't tell you
everything about me.

1415
01:30:00.351 --> 01:30:03.220
I was accused of murder too.
But I ain't kill nobody.

1416
01:30:05.256 --> 01:30:07.224
Dude's name was Dwight Tooley.

1417
01:30:07.258 --> 01:30:09.460
He owed me some dope money.
I went to collect.

1418
01:30:09.493 --> 01:30:12.263
We got into it. Shit got ugly.
He hit his head.

1419
01:30:12.296 --> 01:30:15.165
<i>Next thing I know. police is
arresting me for assault and battery.</i>

1420
01:30:15.199 --> 01:30:18.135
And then two months later.
he dies of a brain aneurysm.

1421
01:30:18.168 --> 01:30:21.171
- An aneurysm can happen at anytime.
- Exactly.

1422
01:30:21.205 --> 01:30:23.574
It's the same shit
my lawyer was trying to say.

1423
01:30:23.607 --> 01:30:26.577
but the family. they wasn't trying
to hear me doing a year for assault.

1424
01:30:26.610 --> 01:30:29.079
so they got the judge to up
my sentence to manslaughter.

1425
01:30:29.580 --> 01:30:33.083
They said if we didn't get into the
fight. then he wouldn't have died.

1426
01:30:33.117 --> 01:30:35.785
They put years on my sentence.

1427
01:30:36.620 --> 01:30:38.222
Years I ain't deserve.

1428
01:30:40.457 --> 01:30:43.294
E. if my brother got anything
to do with this.

1429
01:30:45.129 --> 01:30:48.299
that's never gonna
sit well with me. ever.

1430
01:30:49.633 --> 01:30:52.603
But I don't want to lose you
to this. E.

1431
01:30:52.636 --> 01:30:55.973
I don't want to lose you to this shit.
I don't want to lose you to nothing.

1432
01:31:00.611 --> 01:31:03.047
I'm so sorry
this happened to us.

1433
01:31:09.253 --> 01:31:10.954
I love you so much.

1434
01:31:10.988 --> 01:31:12.523
Come back to me. baby.

1435
01:31:13.357 --> 01:31:15.225
God... No. I can't.

1436
01:31:15.926 --> 01:31:18.095
- Come back to me.
- I can't. Not with this...

1437
01:31:18.128 --> 01:31:19.463
Not with this going on.

1438
01:31:19.496 --> 01:31:21.231
[horn honks]

1439
01:31:23.567 --> 01:31:24.868
[sighs]

1440
01:31:26.203 --> 01:31:27.571
[Marcus] Really?

1441
01:31:28.072 --> 01:31:30.341
Got a nigga picking you up
that quick?

1442
01:31:33.377 --> 01:31:35.212
If that's what you think.

1443
01:31:36.180 --> 01:31:39.283
then you never got
how much I cared about you.

1444
01:31:45.189 --> 01:31:46.457
He's my cousin.

1445
01:31:54.665 --> 01:31:57.201
[car departs]

1446
01:31:58.102 --> 01:31:59.536
[knocking on door]

1447
01:32:14.084 --> 01:32:16.186
[knocking continues]

1448
01:32:20.624 --> 01:32:22.159
What are you doing here?

1449
01:32:22.926 --> 01:32:25.095
I'd like to talk to you
about your brother.

1450
01:32:27.464 --> 01:32:30.033
- [high-pitched ringing]
- [Marcus] <i>You're telling me the same gun</i>

1451
01:32:30.067 --> 01:32:31.668
<i>that killed Stacy and Al.
is the same gun</i>

1452
01:32:31.702 --> 01:32:33.470
- <i>that killed the Gerviches?</i>
- [Joe] <i>Yeah.</i>

1453
01:32:34.204 --> 01:32:36.306
Doesn't mean the gun
didn't belong to either of 'em.

1454
01:32:36.340 --> 01:32:38.575
But it wasn't a murder-suicide.

1455
01:32:38.609 --> 01:32:41.044
Someone else wanted them
shut down.

1456
01:32:41.078 --> 01:32:44.114
- [ringing fades]
- Instead of you following leads. you drop over here with coffee?

1457
01:32:44.782 --> 01:32:47.384
[chuckles]
Yeah. with good reason.

1458
01:32:47.418 --> 01:32:50.053
Those bullets led me back
to the night

1459
01:32:50.087 --> 01:32:52.356
that they were all brought in.

1460
01:32:54.158 --> 01:32:56.293
Most importantly. Drew.

1461
01:32:56.326 --> 01:32:57.561
Why is that?

1462
01:32:57.594 --> 01:32:59.997
Because of how
he talked about you.

1463
01:33:00.397 --> 01:33:03.200
He... He mentioned me?

1464
01:33:03.233 --> 01:33:08.639
He never mentioned you by name.
but uh. wow. you know.

1465
01:33:08.672 --> 01:33:12.976
once he started tearing you apart. he...
he couldn't stop.

1466
01:33:13.010 --> 01:33:16.113
How could you know he was talking about me?
He's got three brothers.

1467
01:33:16.146 --> 01:33:19.483
Only one's an addict
and did jail time.

1468
01:33:23.020 --> 01:33:24.354
He covered everything.

1469
01:33:24.788 --> 01:33:26.156
Like what?

1470
01:33:27.057 --> 01:33:29.293
He said he felt like
he was living your life

1471
01:33:29.326 --> 01:33:31.328
now that shit had
gotten better for you.

1472
01:33:31.995 --> 01:33:34.264
He lost his job.
he lost his girlfriend.

1473
01:33:34.298 --> 01:33:37.267
he was being dragged into
a bullshit murder charge.

1474
01:33:37.301 --> 01:33:39.736
which he... he wasn't mad about.

1475
01:33:40.337 --> 01:33:44.775
But when I asked him
if he was living two lives.

1476
01:33:44.808 --> 01:33:46.143
boom.

1477
01:33:48.045 --> 01:33:49.513
He went into his brother.

1478
01:33:49.546 --> 01:33:51.348
If you think
Drew's behind all of this.

1479
01:33:51.381 --> 01:33:52.716
then fucking arrest him.

1480
01:33:57.087 --> 01:33:59.490
[sighs]
That would be a waste of time.

1481
01:34:00.324 --> 01:34:04.361
The more missteps you make in a
homicide case. the more messy it gets.

1482
01:34:04.394 --> 01:34:06.563
And I don't...
I don't fucking do messy.

1483
01:34:06.597 --> 01:34:08.599
Like you being here right now
ain't messy?

1484
01:34:08.632 --> 01:34:11.201
You know... [clears throat]

1485
01:34:11.235 --> 01:34:13.437
...my mother told me
when I was a kid that

1486
01:34:13.470 --> 01:34:16.039
the biggest Christian
was probably the biggest sinner

1487
01:34:16.073 --> 01:34:21.078
and that the second they
took Jesus into their heart.

1488
01:34:21.111 --> 01:34:24.248
that's when they could only
see in black and white.

1489
01:34:25.849 --> 01:34:29.553
You know who else
is super judgmental?

1490
01:34:31.388 --> 01:34:33.657
Addicts who get clean.

1491
01:34:34.691 --> 01:34:37.327
The anonymous caller

1492
01:34:37.361 --> 01:34:39.363
was someone
who wanted a reward.

1493
01:34:39.396 --> 01:34:41.365
Someone who wanted to do right.

1494
01:34:43.534 --> 01:34:46.403
There was no reward
being offered. Marcus.

1495
01:34:46.436 --> 01:34:48.372
What you trying to say?

1496
01:34:48.405 --> 01:34:49.773
You think it was me?

1497
01:34:52.809 --> 01:34:56.346
I'm just trying to see
where the puzzle pieces fit.

1498
01:34:56.380 --> 01:34:58.682
I'm sorry. bro. It wasn't me.

1499
01:35:01.652 --> 01:35:04.755
My first year as a detective.

1500
01:35:05.322 --> 01:35:07.558
I knew that if I could
get information

1501
01:35:07.591 --> 01:35:11.295
from a murderer's wife.
I could close the case.

1502
01:35:11.828 --> 01:35:14.364
but every time I tried to talk to
her. she shut me out.

1503
01:35:14.398 --> 01:35:17.568
I mean. he was abusive.
but she was...

1504
01:35:18.569 --> 01:35:20.203
she was ride or die.

1505
01:35:21.305 --> 01:35:24.408
So one day I waited for the
husband to leave and. um...

1506
01:35:27.277 --> 01:35:31.281
I remember I brought her a carton
of her favorite cigarettes.

1507
01:35:32.115 --> 01:35:34.718
And within 20 minutes
of sitting on her couch.

1508
01:35:34.751 --> 01:35:38.555
she told me everything.
because I just happened to show up

1509
01:35:38.589 --> 01:35:40.657
right after
he put hands on her.

1510
01:35:42.259 --> 01:35:44.661
When people have information

1511
01:35:44.695 --> 01:35:48.131
that they really wanna share.

1512
01:35:48.732 --> 01:35:51.201
they're hoping that somebody
will coax it out of 'em.

1513
01:35:51.234 --> 01:35:54.504
It is my job to catch them
at the right time.

1514
01:35:55.073 --> 01:35:57.407
Ain't none of that shit
my concern.

1515
01:35:58.241 --> 01:36:01.378
Drew was with my brother.
Anthony. that night.

1516
01:36:03.614 --> 01:36:05.849
- So I guess you came here for nothing.
- I disagree.

1517
01:36:05.883 --> 01:36:08.218
I think you know more
than you're letting on.

1518
01:36:08.251 --> 01:36:10.153
Too bad I don't smoke.

1519
01:36:11.421 --> 01:36:15.258
Well. most alcoholics
turn to coffee

1520
01:36:15.927 --> 01:36:17.694
when they quit drinking.

1521
01:36:20.932 --> 01:36:22.299
All right.

1522
01:36:24.701 --> 01:36:25.769
[exhales]

1523
01:36:27.972 --> 01:36:30.841
Does Drew own a .45?

1524
01:36:32.977 --> 01:36:34.378
No.

1525
01:36:39.449 --> 01:36:41.752
Whether you believe me or not.
this is my last fucking case.

1526
01:36:41.785 --> 01:36:42.786
I...

1527
01:36:43.955 --> 01:36:46.256
I've really grown tired
of this shit.

1528
01:36:48.759 --> 01:36:50.427
Because at some point...

1529
01:36:57.300 --> 01:36:59.436
most of the cases I've had...

1530
01:37:01.605 --> 01:37:04.808
they end with either a Black
man holding a gun in his hand

1531
01:37:04.841 --> 01:37:06.843
or inside the chalk lines.

1532
01:37:11.883 --> 01:37:13.684
Fucking wearing on me.

1533
01:37:15.920 --> 01:37:19.489
It's eating me alive.
It makes it hard to fucking sleep.

1534
01:37:23.928 --> 01:37:25.897
How's that for oversharing?

1535
01:37:30.267 --> 01:37:31.334
All right.

1536
01:37:35.472 --> 01:37:36.707
[sighs]

1537
01:37:38.375 --> 01:37:39.944
How do you sleep. Marcus?

1538
01:37:44.448 --> 01:37:45.549
Yeah.

1539
01:37:47.751 --> 01:37:49.686
[door opens]

1540
01:37:51.822 --> 01:37:52.890
[door closes]

1541
01:37:57.461 --> 01:37:59.997
[phone buzzing]

1542
01:38:01.598 --> 01:38:03.700
[buzzing continues]

1543
01:38:10.540 --> 01:38:12.375
Finally. my brother calls.

1544
01:38:13.310 --> 01:38:16.279
Tell Mama and Daddy
I'll be by for Sunday dinner.

1545
01:38:16.313 --> 01:38:19.683
Now you're talking. Sound like you're
serious too. You're gonna really be there?

1546
01:38:19.716 --> 01:38:22.285
You gonna be there?
[chuckles]

1547
01:38:22.786 --> 01:38:25.322
- All right. bro. later.
- <i>All right. I love you. brother.</i>

1548
01:38:32.662 --> 01:38:35.398
[no audible dialogue]

1549
01:39:18.475 --> 01:39:20.878
[Belinda] You really don't
watch reality shows?

1550
01:39:20.912 --> 01:39:23.380
- [both] No.
- [Belinda] I've learned a lot from them.

1551
01:39:23.413 --> 01:39:26.383
How to center myself.
not depend on a man.

1552
01:39:26.416 --> 01:39:28.819
- get myself out of debt.
- [Tisha] Okay. wait a minute. I thought you said

1553
01:39:28.853 --> 01:39:30.988
<i>Skanks on the Boulevard</i>
was your favorite show.

1554
01:39:31.022 --> 01:39:34.058
- Mm-hmm.
- [Tish] Please tell me what in the hell you learned from that?

1555
01:39:34.091 --> 01:39:36.827
Well. all of those women
overcame their situations.

1556
01:39:36.861 --> 01:39:38.996
[Loren chuckles]

1557
01:39:39.030 --> 01:39:42.666
You know. people who watch reality
shows usually end up jobless.

1558
01:39:42.699 --> 01:39:44.969
[mouthing word]

1559
01:39:45.002 --> 01:39:48.538
- [toilet flushes]
- [chattering. arguing]

1560
01:39:50.141 --> 01:39:51.641
[Lloyd] Terry.

1561
01:39:52.509 --> 01:39:55.745
What was that John Wayne movie
you used to like

1562
01:39:55.779 --> 01:39:58.149
when you was a kid? Um...

1563
01:39:58.182 --> 01:40:00.852
- [Terry] <i>Stagecoach.</i>
- <i>Stagecoach.</i> That's it. That's it.

1564
01:40:00.885 --> 01:40:02.419
[laughing]

1565
01:40:02.452 --> 01:40:04.387
You used to say.
"When I grow up.

1566
01:40:04.421 --> 01:40:06.057
I want to be a white cowboy."

1567
01:40:06.090 --> 01:40:08.592
- [all laughing]
- Did I say white?

1568
01:40:08.625 --> 01:40:11.162
[Lloyd] Yeah. you said white.
Well. that's all you saw on TV then.

1569
01:40:11.195 --> 01:40:14.564
- [Terry] I said I wanted to be a white cowboy?
- [Lloyd] White cowboy.

1570
01:40:14.598 --> 01:40:15.632
You good?

1571
01:40:16.100 --> 01:40:17.367
Yeah.

1572
01:40:19.636 --> 01:40:21.605
Bad shit happens. Marcus.

1573
01:40:22.306 --> 01:40:23.840
Sometimes
you're on the giving end.

1574
01:40:23.875 --> 01:40:25.675
sometimes
you're on the receiving.

1575
01:40:25.709 --> 01:40:26.843
Hmm.

1576
01:40:27.444 --> 01:40:29.512
Which end were Stacy and Al?

1577
01:40:31.148 --> 01:40:33.383
The end of unnecessary bullshit.

1578
01:40:35.152 --> 01:40:36.519
We good?

1579
01:40:44.661 --> 01:40:47.031
[chattering. laughing]

1580
01:40:47.064 --> 01:40:49.000
[Lloyd] Oh. here they come.
Here they come.

1581
01:40:53.536 --> 01:40:54.671
Okay.

1582
01:40:57.975 --> 01:40:59.977
- Terry. go ahead. say the grace.
- [Terry] Yes. sir.

1583
01:41:00.011 --> 01:41:00.912
Dad.

1584
01:41:03.080 --> 01:41:05.782
- [whispers] Marcus...
- Come on. man. I'm only gonna say something like...

1585
01:41:09.786 --> 01:41:13.490
- You know. why don't we get Marcus to pray?
- [Lloyd] Okay. Marcus.

1586
01:41:16.060 --> 01:41:19.096
No. I usually keep my prayers
to myself.

1587
01:41:19.130 --> 01:41:20.730
or my AA group.

1588
01:41:22.832 --> 01:41:24.936
Baby. you've been
drinking again?

1589
01:41:24.969 --> 01:41:26.938
[laughs]

1590
01:41:26.971 --> 01:41:28.973
You sure know your son. huh?

1591
01:41:30.241 --> 01:41:32.109
It's been a rough few days.
Mama.

1592
01:41:36.546 --> 01:41:38.182
Can I talk to you outside?

1593
01:41:38.215 --> 01:41:39.951
- Mm-hmm. yeah.
- [Lloyd] What's going on now?

1594
01:41:39.984 --> 01:41:41.518
[Anthony] Drew.

1595
01:41:41.551 --> 01:41:42.686
Excuse us.

1596
01:41:43.287 --> 01:41:44.521
[sighs]

1597
01:41:47.657 --> 01:41:48.792
I'll wait.

1598
01:41:51.162 --> 01:41:52.462
Wait for what?

1599
01:41:53.164 --> 01:41:55.066
What's going on here?

1600
01:41:56.067 --> 01:41:57.534
You'll see.

1601
01:41:58.302 --> 01:41:59.803
[door opens]

1602
01:42:03.140 --> 01:42:04.674
Come on. we out.

1603
01:42:04.708 --> 01:42:07.211
Did I do something?
What's going on?

1604
01:42:07.244 --> 01:42:09.679
He's drunk.
I don't want you to see that shit.

1605
01:42:09.713 --> 01:42:12.116
and I don't wanna stick around
to hear that. all right?

1606
01:42:12.149 --> 01:42:14.218
Do you think he'll
say something about you?

1607
01:42:17.154 --> 01:42:18.788
Why don't you take the car?

1608
01:42:19.390 --> 01:42:21.524
Let me go back
and hear what happens.

1609
01:42:22.259 --> 01:42:24.295
Okay?
I'ma call you.

1610
01:42:24.328 --> 01:42:26.830
[door opens. closes]

1611
01:42:31.202 --> 01:42:33.070
She ain't family
and I didn't want her to see

1612
01:42:33.104 --> 01:42:35.139
Marcus make an ass
out of himself.

1613
01:42:37.640 --> 01:42:39.010
So go ahead. bro.

1614
01:42:46.350 --> 01:42:49.320
You know. I really thought
I found some light

1615
01:42:49.353 --> 01:42:50.955
when I met Eva.

1616
01:42:52.256 --> 01:42:54.859
When you got me that job
driving the bus. Pop.

1617
01:42:55.759 --> 01:42:57.228
yeah. I really thought...

1618
01:42:59.030 --> 01:43:00.563
I turned the corner.

1619
01:43:02.333 --> 01:43:04.969
That all went to hell
once I seen that boy on TV.

1620
01:43:05.002 --> 01:43:08.939
Son. we already
talked about this.

1621
01:43:09.806 --> 01:43:11.175
What little boy?

1622
01:43:11.208 --> 01:43:13.110
[Marcus] The Gervich boy.

1623
01:43:13.144 --> 01:43:16.013
He was on TV
talking about this. uh.

1624
01:43:16.047 --> 01:43:19.616
collection of baseball cards
that his father had for him.

1625
01:43:19.649 --> 01:43:22.019
and how they was stolen.

1626
01:43:22.420 --> 01:43:25.289
Marcus. why are you bringing
that shit up. man? Hmm?

1627
01:43:25.990 --> 01:43:28.259
- This shit is over. bro.
- Watch your mouth. boy.

1628
01:43:28.292 --> 01:43:29.960
Watch your mouth.
You still at my table.

1629
01:43:29.994 --> 01:43:31.996
[Marcus] I asked you
where the cards from.

1630
01:43:32.029 --> 01:43:35.266
You said Stacy gave 'em
to you for safekeeping.

1631
01:43:35.299 --> 01:43:37.834
I didn't know if he was telling
the truth 'cause with those dudes.

1632
01:43:37.868 --> 01:43:40.637
you can get caught up in
something you can't say no to.

1633
01:43:40.670 --> 01:43:43.040
But I wanted to protect you.

1634
01:43:46.911 --> 01:43:48.946
So I called in
that anonymous tip.

1635
01:43:48.979 --> 01:43:50.948
[Drew] Nigga. you drunk.
Mama. he drunk.

1636
01:43:50.981 --> 01:43:52.816
Look at him.
It's embarrassing.

1637
01:43:52.849 --> 01:43:54.885
coming in the house drunk like
that. lying and shit.

1638
01:43:54.919 --> 01:43:56.653
- [Lloyd] Drew.
- That's embarrassing. Daddy.

1639
01:43:56.686 --> 01:43:58.755
- It's fucking embarr...
- [Lloyd] Hey. Drew.

1640
01:44:03.827 --> 01:44:07.965
What is Marcus saying here?

1641
01:44:10.733 --> 01:44:12.702
Don't you lie to me.

1642
01:44:15.906 --> 01:44:18.775
He was with Al and Stacy the
night those people got murdered.

1643
01:44:19.809 --> 01:44:21.245
[Della] Wait a minute. son.

1644
01:44:22.379 --> 01:44:25.849
You were with Al and Stacy

1645
01:44:26.484 --> 01:44:30.354
the night that they
murdered those people?

1646
01:44:31.088 --> 01:44:33.324
Goddamn it. boy!

1647
01:44:33.357 --> 01:44:36.826
You gave me those cards to hold
and you lied to me!

1648
01:44:36.861 --> 01:44:39.296
- Della. Della...
- What do you mean? You knew about this?

1649
01:44:39.330 --> 01:44:42.665
Lloyd. he gave me the cards.
He asked me to hold them. 'cause he said

1650
01:44:42.699 --> 01:44:44.401
Stacy was gonna try to pin
the murder on him.

1651
01:44:44.435 --> 01:44:46.871
- Wait a minute.
- [Della] But he swore to me

1652
01:44:46.904 --> 01:44:49.440
- that he didn't have anything to do with it.
- [Lloyd] Do you know...

1653
01:44:49.473 --> 01:44:53.978
[Della] Are you that low that you
would take another person's life?

1654
01:44:54.011 --> 01:44:56.713
Did we not teach you
anything. boy?

1655
01:44:56.746 --> 01:44:59.749
- [Lloyd] You knew about this?
- Yes. Lloyd. I knew!

1656
01:44:59.782 --> 01:45:02.286
Well. what did you do
with the cards?

1657
01:45:02.319 --> 01:45:03.921
I burned them. Lloyd.

1658
01:45:03.954 --> 01:45:06.323
When you went into the hospital.
I burned them.

1659
01:45:07.358 --> 01:45:09.093
Why didn't you tell me about it?

1660
01:45:09.126 --> 01:45:10.995
'Cause I was trying
to save our son.

1661
01:45:11.028 --> 01:45:12.997
- "Save our son"?
- Man. why are you doing this?

1662
01:45:13.030 --> 01:45:15.866
- Save your son? What about saving your...
- Man. shut the fuck up!

1663
01:45:15.900 --> 01:45:18.035
And you brought
our mom into this?

1664
01:45:18.068 --> 01:45:19.802
Why you doing this. man?

1665
01:45:20.237 --> 01:45:22.907
That cop said that the same gun
that killed that family

1666
01:45:22.940 --> 01:45:26.076
killed Al and Stacy. nigga.

1667
01:45:26.110 --> 01:45:27.411
No. no. no.

1668
01:45:27.444 --> 01:45:30.813
A .45. like the one you own!

1669
01:45:33.918 --> 01:45:34.885
Drew.

1670
01:45:37.221 --> 01:45:38.289
Drew.

1671
01:45:39.857 --> 01:45:41.824
What in God's name
did you do?

1672
01:45:42.526 --> 01:45:45.930
[Lloyd] Son. Come on.

1673
01:45:47.830 --> 01:45:49.732
Come on. baby.

1674
01:45:50.401 --> 01:45:51.502
Come on. baby.

1675
01:45:51.535 --> 01:45:52.937
[sniffles]

1676
01:45:54.271 --> 01:45:56.739
So I guess... [sniffles]

1677
01:45:56.773 --> 01:45:58.943
I guess I'm the black sheep
now. right?

1678
01:45:58.976 --> 01:46:00.444
- Huh?
- No.

1679
01:46:00.477 --> 01:46:02.479
Are you happy. huh?
Are you fucking happy?

1680
01:46:02.513 --> 01:46:05.382
- [all screaming]
- [grunting]

1681
01:46:05.416 --> 01:46:07.418
[shouting]

1682
01:46:09.353 --> 01:46:11.355
[screaming. crying]

1683
01:46:11.388 --> 01:46:12.856
[grunts]

1684
01:46:15.926 --> 01:46:17.861
[Anthony] Stay the fuck down.
Stay down.

1685
01:46:17.895 --> 01:46:19.363
[grunts]

1686
01:46:19.396 --> 01:46:21.831
Don't get up. bro.
Don't get up.

1687
01:46:21.865 --> 01:46:24.767
- [Lloyd] It's not that bad.
- [Marcus groans]

1688
01:46:24.801 --> 01:46:26.803
[Lloyd] She... She call 911?

1689
01:46:26.836 --> 01:46:29.106
[Terry] Yeah. she called.
She called. Tisha!

1690
01:46:29.139 --> 01:46:33.010
- [Della sobbing]
- Okay. it's okay. It's okay.

1691
01:46:33.611 --> 01:46:36.180
It's okay. boy.
I love you.

1692
01:46:37.281 --> 01:46:40.084
I love you.
You're gonna be fine.

1693
01:46:40.117 --> 01:46:44.555
You did good. You did good.
You did right.

1694
01:46:44.588 --> 01:46:46.823
[melancholy piano music playing]

1695
01:46:57.334 --> 01:46:59.470
[siren wailing]

1696
01:47:24.495 --> 01:47:26.230
[music continues]

1697
01:47:31.368 --> 01:47:33.404
[no audible dialogue]

1698
01:47:56.026 --> 01:47:58.195
[music continues]

1699
01:48:40.137 --> 01:48:41.271
[sniffles]

1700
01:49:01.091 --> 01:49:03.327
[monitor beeping]

1701
01:49:08.265 --> 01:49:09.500
Morning.

1702
01:49:12.336 --> 01:49:14.104
[gasps] Marcus.

1703
01:49:14.671 --> 01:49:17.441
Marcus. Oh. baby.

1704
01:49:17.474 --> 01:49:18.675
[Marcus] Hey. Mama.

1705
01:49:22.212 --> 01:49:23.947
[Lloyd] Hey. boy.

1706
01:49:23.981 --> 01:49:26.550
Hey. there. Hey. there.
Hey. there. Hey. there.

1707
01:49:26.583 --> 01:49:28.685
Hey. boy. [laughing]

1708
01:49:28.719 --> 01:49:32.189
- That's my boy. How you feeling?
- I'm all right.

1709
01:49:32.222 --> 01:49:33.290
- You all right?
- Yeah.

1710
01:49:33.323 --> 01:49:34.625
- [Lloyd] Yeah.
- Baby.

1711
01:49:34.658 --> 01:49:36.460
[Lloyd] He's gonna be all right.

1712
01:49:36.493 --> 01:49:38.429
- He's gonna be all right.
- [knocking on door]

1713
01:49:38.462 --> 01:49:39.630
Morning.

1714
01:49:41.432 --> 01:49:42.599
May we help you?

1715
01:49:45.102 --> 01:49:48.038
Here to have a conversation
with your son.

1716
01:49:48.705 --> 01:49:51.442
- Marcus. who is this?
- That's the cop who arrested Drew.

1717
01:49:51.475 --> 01:49:52.676
What you doing here?

1718
01:49:55.312 --> 01:49:57.448
[sighs] Marcus. I. um...

1719
01:49:57.948 --> 01:50:00.184
I'ma keep this simple for you.

1720
01:50:00.717 --> 01:50:02.486
If your brother's attempt
to kill you

1721
01:50:02.519 --> 01:50:04.221
had anything to do with
the Gerviches...

1722
01:50:04.254 --> 01:50:06.290
Nobody gives a damn
about the Gerviches.

1723
01:50:06.858 --> 01:50:09.259
...he might not get charged
with a home invasion.

1724
01:50:11.028 --> 01:50:13.397
But filing charges
will make sure

1725
01:50:13.430 --> 01:50:15.699
that he pays for this
in some way.

1726
01:50:17.634 --> 01:50:20.471
- If you press charges...
- [Della] So you want him to do your job.

1727
01:50:20.504 --> 01:50:24.141
- [Anthony] Mom. Mom...
- Just do your own goddamn job and leave us alone!

1728
01:50:24.174 --> 01:50:26.543
Della. stop it.

1729
01:50:28.045 --> 01:50:32.249
Yeah. If Drew did this crime.

1730
01:50:32.282 --> 01:50:34.251
- then he's gonna have to pay.
- Really. Lloyd?

1731
01:50:34.284 --> 01:50:36.019
- Really.
- Dad. calm down.

1732
01:50:36.053 --> 01:50:37.488
- Don't "Dad" me.
- Do we need to do this?

1733
01:50:37.521 --> 01:50:39.256
- Stay out of it!
- We do not have to do this.

1734
01:50:39.289 --> 01:50:41.358
- [Della] Lloyd!
- [Terry] Everybody calm down!

1735
01:50:41.391 --> 01:50:44.461
- Ma. Ma. Ma. Pop.
- [Lloyd] How can I? Don't tell us to calm down.

1736
01:50:45.362 --> 01:50:46.530
Y'all. stop.

1737
01:51:14.491 --> 01:51:16.059
It's my family.

1738
01:51:21.365 --> 01:51:23.066
It's my brother.

1739
01:51:54.631 --> 01:51:56.667
[downtempo pop music playing]

